#. type: Title ===
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introspecting a Requesting Party Token"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sometimes you might want to introspect a requesting party token (RPT) to check its validity or obtain the permissions within the token to enforce authorization decisions on the resource server side.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "There are two main use cases where token introspection can help you:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "When client applications need to query the token validity to obtain a new one with the same or additional permissions\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "When enforcing authorization decisions at the resource server side, especially when none of the built-in <<_enforcer_overview, policy enforcers>> fits your application\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining Information about an RPT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "The token introspection is essentially a https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7662[OAuth2 token introspection]-compliant endpoint from which you can obtain information about an RPT.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "```bash\n"
"http://${host}:${port}/auth/realms/${realm_name}/protocol/openid-connect/token/introspect\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "To introspect an RPT using this endpoint, you can send a request to the server as follows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "```bash\n"
"curl -X POST \\\n"
"    -H \"Authorization: Basic aGVsbG8td29ybGQtYXV0aHotc2VydmljZTpzZWNyZXQ=\" \\\n"
"    -H \"Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\" \\\n"
"    -d 'token_type_hint=requesting_party_token&token=${RPT}' \\\n"
"    \"http://localhost:8080/auth/realms/hello-world-authz/protocol/openid-connect/token/introspect\"\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "The request above is using HTTP BASIC and passing the client's credentials (client ID and secret) to authenticate the client attempting to introspect the token, but you can use any other client authentication method supported by {project_name}.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "The introspection endpoint expects two parameters:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "*token_type_hint*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use *requesting_party_token* as the value for this parameter, which indicates that you want to introspect an RPT.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "*token*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use the token string as it was returned by the server during the authorization process as the value for this parameter.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "```json\n"
"{\n"
"  \"permissions\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"resource_set_id\": \"90ccc6fc-b296-4cd1-881e-089e1ee15957\",\n"
"      \"resource_set_name\": \"Hello World Resource\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"exp\": 1465314139,\n"
"  \"nbf\": 0,\n"
"  \"iat\": 1465313839,\n"
"  \"aud\": \"hello-world-authz-service\",\n"
"  \"active\": true\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "If the RPT is not active, this response is returned instead:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "```json\n"
"{\n"
"  \"active\": false\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "Do I Need to Invoke the Server Every Time I Want to Introspect an RPT?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "No. Both <<_service_entitlement_api, Entitlement>> APIs use the\n"
" https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519[JSON web token (JWT)] specification as the default format for RPTs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:75
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you want to validate these tokens without a call to the remote introspection endpoint, you can decode the RPT and query for its validity locally. Once you decode the token,\n"
"you can also use the permissions within the token to enforce authorization decisions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:77
#, no-wrap
msgid "This is essentially what the <<_enforcer_overview, policy enforcers>> do. Be sure to:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "Validate the signature of the RPT (based on the realm's public key)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/token-introspection.adoc:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "Query for token validity based on its _exp_, _iat_, and _aud_ claims\n"
msgstr ""

